Don't include absolute filenames in binaries

The kbuild utilities are compiled with absolute patch names, so
paths starting with $RPM_BUILD_ROOT would end up in the binaries.
To avoid this, remove all references to __FILE__ (direct and
indirect via assert()).

  Andreas Gruenbacher <agruen@suse.de>, SUSE Labs

